<TEXT>
two quirky series with cult 
followings were among television series showered with emmy award 
nominations 
but once again heavyweight housewife roseanne barr failed to 
impress the academy of television arts amp sciences 
abcs offbeat twin peaks the critically acclaimed but 
poorly rated saga of sex murder and cherry pie in a fictional 
pacific northwest logging town snared an industryleading 14 emmy 
nominations thursday 
the simpsons fox broadcasting cos cartoon chronicle of a 
grumbling american family collected five nominations three for 
primetime series and two for a christmas special 
twin peaks was nominated as outstanding drama series the 
shows executive producers david lynch and mark frost shared a 
nomination for best writing lynch the auteur filmmaker also was 
nominated for best drama directing 
were just delighted to be in the position we have suddenly 
found ourselves in said frost frankly the whole thing has 
sort of been out of left field and this is the icing on the cake 
the emmy nominations also could bring added respectability to 
the simpsons featuring wisecracking 10yearold bart simpson 
who vaulted to national prominence with a rebellious attitude and 
resurrected american slang phrases like dont have a cow man 
the show has been criticized for its often cynical portrayal of the 
american family 
simpsons executive producer james l brooks said he was in 
a sleepy sweaty puddle when awakened with news of the academy of 
television arts amp sciences nominations announced during a predawn 
ceremony by actor louis gosset jr and china beach star dana 
delany 
abcs toprated roseanne received two selections one for 
costar john goodman as best supporting actor but barr was snubbed 
by academy voters who also ignored the controversial comic in last 
years nominations 
it always takes the industry a few years to catch up with 
anything groundbreaking said barrs husband tom arnold 
barr wouldnt comment earlier this week she told talk show host 
sally jessy raphael that last years snub really my hurt 
feelings but she expected the same this year 
abcs highly rated americas funniest home videos also was 
ignored by the academy proving that top nielsen figures dont 
automatically translate into emmy nominations 
nbcs legal eagles on la law received 13 nominations the 
networks longrunning comedy cheers and cbss hit murphy 
brown both amassed 12 nominations each 
the simpsons was nominated in the category of outstanding 
animated program for programming one hour or less where 
competition included garfield and charlie brown specials 
abc won 95 nominations overall tying it for first with nbc abc 
finished last in the 1989 nominations a position held this year by 
cbs with 73 selections 
upstart fox earned 26 more than double its 12 nominations last 
year another notable fox nominee was in living color a 
highly praised sketch comedy show featuring mostly black performers 
kyle maclachlan the cherry pieloving fbi agent on twin 
peaks was nominated for best actor in a drama series piper 
laurie earned a lead drama actress nomination 
other nominees for best drama series were abcs china beach 
and thirtysomething and nbcs la law and quantum 
leap 
six programs honored thursday wont be on television next 
season foxs the tracey ullman show which earned 13 
nominations cbs newhart beauty and the beast the 
famous teddy z the equalizer and mancuso fbi 
one nomination went to the late muppets creator jim henson who 
was named for directing a variety or music program 
other nominees for best dramatic actor were peter falk of abcs 
columbo edward woodward from cbs the equalizer robert 
loggia in nbcs mancuso fbi and scott bakula of quantum 
leap 
dramatic actress choices included last years winner dana 
delany of china beach jill eikenberry from la law 
angela lansbury for cbs murder she wrote and patricia wettig 
in thirtysomething 
winners will be announced sept 16 at a ceremony in pasadena 
scheduled for broadcast on fox 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

