<TEXT>
a car bomb has exploded near an office of 
the syrianbacked amal militia in this southern port city killing 
eight people and wounding 75 others police said today 
they said the car rigged with 43 pounds of explosives 
detonated in the citys hay alraml district at 11 pm thursday 
a police spokesman in tyre 80 miles south of beirut said the 
casualties occurred when people rushed to check damage caused by a 
small bomb that blew up minutes before the car bomb exploded 
the spokesman who cannot be named in line with regulations 
said one amal militiaman was among the dead and 10 others among the 
wounded 
the car bomb the sixth in lebanon this year came a few hours 
after a boobytrapped car exploded in nabatiyeh killing one person 
and wounding four others 
no one claimed responsibility for either attack 
reporters based in tyre said amal militiamen toured the city in 
cars today urging the population through loudspeakers to observe a 
general strike today to protest what they called an iranian 
massacre 
the daylong strike was called for in amalcontrolled tyre and 
nabatiyeh 18 miles farther south 
amal has been locked in a 3yearold intermittent war with the 
iranianbacked hezbollah or party of god for control of lebanons 
12 million shiite moslems who make up the countrys largest sect 
by police count more than 1000 people have been killed and 
4000 wounded in the power struggle 
</TEXT>
