<DOCNO> AP900803-0038 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the communist party has lost 765000 members so 
far this year leaving it with about 18 million members the 
partys personnel chief says 
boris pugo says 370000 members have joined russian president 
boris yeltsin and other reformers in quitting the party about 
three times the number of membership cards turned in during all of 
1989 
in addition 125000 members were expelled 120000 died and 
150000 stopped paying their membership dues or participating in 
party activities he told tass on wednesday 
in the first six months of this year 125000 new members have 
signed up for a net loss of 765000 members said pugo chairman 
of the partys central control committee 
pugo said many people had joined the party to promote their 
careers soviet president mikhail s gorbachev has moved to 
separate the government from party jobs and affairs since taking 
office in 1985 
as a result the communist party has lost much prestigious along 
with its constitutionally guaranteed leading role in society 
the figures are not large enough to speak about a catastrophe 
or an extraordinary situation in the party pugo told tass it 
is not large enough to cause great concern 
pugo could not say how many people have quit since the partys 
28th congress ended july 13 yeltsin stunned the meeting by 
announcing he was quitting the party to concentrating on governing 
the largest of the 15 soviet republics 
other leading reformers including the mayors of both moscow and 
leningrad have also quit 
party officials said between 120000 and 130000 people resigned 
from the party last year 
</TEXT>
