<TEXT>
an army commando recaptured after escaping 
police custody en route to court to face two rape charges has 
linked himself to nine more rapes in three other states state 
police said 
master sgt marshall l brown 37 was captured unarmed by 
police early thursday in a stolen car in an east providence parking 
lot police found brown through a tip from a confidential source 
the former green beret and ranger escaped monday after freeing 
himself from handcuffs while being taken from a jail to the 
courthouse for a hearing on two charges he raped two cranston 
ri women he faces life in prison if convicted on those charges 
he also had been charged with two rapes in north carolina where 
he was a member of the army special forces stationed at fort bragg 
after he was recaptured brown gave state police information 
linking him to five rapes in north carolina and four others in 
texas and arizona lt brian andrews said brown was cooperative 
andrews said but he stopped short of calling browns remarks a 
confession 
it was not clear whether the five north carolina rapes included 
the two for which brown already had been charged 
brown of spring lake nc was attending a nineweek course at 
the naval education and training center in newport when cranston 
police arrested him on june 11 1989 
the alleged rapes outside rhode island occurred between november 
1988 and may 1989 said attorney general james e oneil he 
declined to be more specific 
oneil said additional charges of escape and theft were expected 
to be filed as early as today 
brown most recently was a member of the delta force the secret 
antiterrorist group and took part in the failed raid to free us 
hostages from iran in 1980 
</TEXT>
