shares on the tokyo stock exchange plummeted as the 
dollar strengthened against the japanese yen today because of 
uncertainties over the iraqkuwait conflict traders said 
the dollar finished trading at 14935 yen up 045 yen from 
thursdays close of 14890 yen after opening at 14977 yen the 
us currency ranged between 14890 yen and 15035 yen 
on the stock market 225issue nikkei stock average shed 72942 
points or 241 percent ending the day at 2951576 it lost 
59281 points thursday 
the drop is because of nothing else but concern over the 
iraqkuwait situation said kenji maeshiro an analyst with 
yamaichi securities co 
the index dropped more than 600 points early in the morning and 
then narrowed the loss to 29171 at the end of the morning session 
it fell back again in the afternoon on a rumor that iraqi troops 
were heading for the border of saudi arabia maeshiro said 
he said largescale arbitrage selling to take profits from price 
differences between the spot and the future markets also fueled the 
plunge in the last 30 minutes of the afternoon session as a result 
of the lastminute massive selling the index ended at the days 
low 
because rumors come out one after another market players just 
could not figure out what was really happening over there and 
growing uncertainties and fears prompted selling maeshiro said 
iraq invaded kuwait and took control of its capital thursday 
japanese participants are sensitive to middle east conditions 
because japan could be hurt more than any other major 
industrialized nation by disruptions in oil supplies 
maeshiro said alreadyrising oil prices also discouraged buying 
because of predictions that higher oil prices would lead to 
inflation and delay possible us action to lower interest rates to 
revitalize its economy 
north sea brent crude oil prices moved sharply higher today as 
the market continued to react to iraqs invasion of kuwait 
by 3 pm brent crude oil for september delivery was at 2300 
to 2330 a barrel or higher than the 2200 late thursday in new 
york earlier thursday in tokyo september brent was valued at 
2260 a barrel 
