yuichi tsuchiko a dealer with fuji bank 
with uncertain prospects in the middle east coupled with rising 
oil prices and a slump in the tokyo stock market tsuchiko said 
many market players adopted a waitandsee position japan depends 
on imports for nearly all its oil needs 
