tropical storm cesar steadily moved across the 
midatlantic today from the coastal african waters where it was 
born 
cesar was just south of the tropic of cancer about 920 miles 
west of the cape verde islands forecaster said they said it was 
moving westnorthwest near 16 mph with maximum sustained winds of 
near 50 mph 
the storm was expected to maintain that motion through saturday 
with little change in strength said forecaster miles lawrence 
its not bothering anybody right now except maybe ships 
said specialist robert molleda of the national hurricane center in 
suburban coral gables 
at 6 am edt today cesar was located near 191 north latitude 
and 398 longitude the center said 
cesar the fourth tropical depression of the atlantic hurricane 
season grew from a tropical wave that formed wednesday afternoon 
on thursday hurricane bertha dissipated after striking the coast 
of newfoundland 
tropical depressions become storms when their top sustained 
winds reach 39 mph the atlantic hurricane season runs from june 1 
through nov 30 
