<TEXT>
unusually hot weather in europe 
has killed five people in spain and caused greeces worst drought 
in 100 years 
between late june and late july temperatures of up to 109 
degrees were recorded twice in the southern region of andalusia 
where three people died because of the heat two more deaths 
occurred in the northwestern city of vigo 
those have been the only fatalities reported so far and 
temperatures in most southern european nations remain well below 
record levels 
