liberties union the justice department and the mexican american 
legal defense and educational fund all plaintiffs in the federal 
lawsuit against los angeles county 
those plans seek to create a hispanic majority district but 
without an incumbent they could overturn the conservative majority 
and possibly lead to profound changes in financing in such areas as 
health and social services programs 
civil rights lawyers today planned to discuss how the plans 
would be implemented 
the county board of supervisors was ordered to redraw the 
districts after kenyon found supervisors violated the federal 
voting rights act by conspiring in 1981 to draw district lines that 
diluted hispanic voting strength 
but the remapping effort approved by the fivemember boards 
