egypt and a council representing saudi 
arabia and five other smaller arab nations today condemned iraqs 
invasion of kuwait and called on baghdad to immediately withdraw 
its troops 
in its denunciation egypt warned that the invasion could have 
dangerous consequences throughout the middle east 
the statement by the gulf cooperation council which includes 
saudi arabia bahrain qatar the united arab emirates oman and 
kuwait contained the first condemnation by saudi arabia which 
borders kuwait 
egypt in a statement issued by its foreign ministry spoke of 
its surprise at iraqs lightning invasion of its small persian gulf 
neighbor 
thursdays invasion came only days after egyptian president 
hosni mubarak stepped in to try to mediate the iraqkuwait dispute 
iraq allowed him to believe his efforts were succeeding 
the egyptian condemnation came as an emergency arab league 
council was preparing to reconvene in cairo to discuss the crisis 
the council at kuwaits request met thursday for six hours but 
issued no statement and adjourned its meeting for 24 hours 
on the day of the invasion the arab world was conspicuously 
silent except to warn against foreign intervention in kuwait 
egyptian government sources speaking on condition of anonymity 
have said mubarak and other arab leaders were initially reluctant 
to condemn iraq because they hoped the situation could be resolved 
without the use of more force 
