<TEXT>
swift action to freeze kuwaiti assets 
overseas after iraqs invasion of its oilrich neighbor will 
prevent strongman saddam hussein from reaping immediate economic 
benefits 
if western nations also take additional moves to cut iraqs oil 
lifeline baghdads already strapped economy will be dealt a harsh 
blow 
the united states took the lead by freezing billions of dollars 
of kuwaiti and iraqi assets banning imports of iraqi oil and 
imposing other trade sanctions oil accounts for 97 percent of 
iraqs exports to the united states 
kuwait had about 42 billion invested in the united states at 
the end of 1989 and iraq had almost nothing invested according to 
the us department of commerce 
britain and france froze kuwaiti assets to keep the countrys 
