the manned spacecraft soyuz tm10 docked with the 
orbiting mir space station on friday two days after it was 
launched the soviet news agency tass reported 
the docking was made neatly and precisely on time tass said 
flight commander lt col gennady manakov and engineer gennady 
strekalov will spend one week working with the old crew which has 
been on board since feb 11 
they replace cosmonauts anatoly solovyev and alexander balandin 
who are scheduled to return to earth on aug 9 following a mission 
plagued by problems with the spacecrafts thermal insulation and a 
broken hatch 
watching from mission control center were two employees of the 
tokyo broadcasting system who are vying to fly into space in 
december television camerawoman ryoko kikuchi and former 
washington bureau chief toyohiro akiyama 
manakov and strekalov will spend 132 days in the mir and will 
conduct 250 experiments including the growing of pure crystals to 
be used as semiconductors and computer chips they will make at 
least two space walks tass said 
their craft was launched wednesday from the baikonur space 
center in soviet central asia 
