<TEXT>
government troops and rebels loyal to 
prince johnson fired rockets and shells friday in blockbyblock 
fighting for the ravaged liberian capital 
the bodies of several pedestrians killed by the crossfire were 
left lying on the sidewalk 
branches were blown off trees damaged downtown shop fronts were 
blasted anew by the indiscriminate firing 
the clashes followed a oneday lull in the 7monthold civil 
war when johnsons men had apparently pulled back to face a 
possible threat from forces loyal to rival rebel leader charles 
taylor 
there was no sign that taylors men had progressed from the 
suburb of paynesville six miles east of the city where they have 
been blocked by president samuel does troops for more than a month 
artillery shells started a fire several blocks away from a huge 
exibition building that was razed thursday no firefighters were 
seen and the blaze raged unchecked 
rockets and shells were fired at the city center by both sides 
as the front line repeatedly shifted from street to street 
reporters cruising by car through the deserted streets briefly 
came under fire but the source of the shooting could not be 
determined 
on bushrod island several thousand hungry people stood in line 
in hope of buying a ticket that would get them a bag of rice one 
woman said she had been waiting for three days 
most of monrovias 500000 inhabitants have been without food 
running water or electricity since last month 
about 5000 people mostly civilians have died since rebels 
invaded from neighboring ivory coast in december the rebels accuse 
doe who took power in a 1980 coup of corruption and human rights 
abuses 
the insurgents have since split into two factions those led by 
johnson and those of taylor who led the original invasion 
johnsons army has emerged as the stronger force according to 
foreign diplomats 
a peace feeler was put out by one of does ministers who asked 
that his name not be used he said he was eager to talk to johnson 
about possible ways to end the fighting which is killing untold 
numbers of people 
the minister stressed the offer would include does 
unconditional resignation but would require the nomination of a 
provisional government 
he cant resign without having someone replace him the 
minister said but he said he was acting on his own initiative and 
had not advised doe of his move 
johnson informed of the proposal at his headquarters in a 
roadside cafe on bushrod island scorned the ministers offer and 
said he was interested only in getting doe not in his maneuvers 
to save himself 
when i get him he will be put on trial for killing 
liberians he said but if he is convicted we will imprison him 
for life we will not kill him 
on monday up to 600 civilian refugees were killed in a lutheran 
church compound witnesses said the slayings were committed by 
government troops doe said rebels dressed as government soldiers 
were to blame 
the victims were members of the gio and mano tribes from which 
the rebels get most of their support soldiers accused of the 
massacre were said by witnesses to belong to does krahn tribe or 
the mandingo tribe 
