cross the border closed to them for 46 years for a friendly 
soccer game in the arctic border village of kirkenes norway not a 
goal was scored in the match 
we wanted to ease the tension a little bit said norwegian 
border commissioner hugo overgaard 
the opposing soldiers mainly young conscripts usually scowl 
and grab for weapons upon sighting each other anywhere along the 
120mile fenced frontier in the far north 
this summer was marked by border incidents including soviet 
troops chasing and shooting at fishermen in norwegian territory 
the tensions seemed to fade when the uniformed soldiers met on 
the border slapped each others backs and exchanged smiles and 
addresses reported the norwegian news agency ntb 
this is the high point of my military service said border 
guard igor gerasimov one of 11 soviet players i hope the border 
can be even more open in the future he told ntb 
the norwegian and soviet troops marched into kirkenes a 15 
minute walk from the border to look around before the game 
its small but interesting said gerasimov there are so 
many products for sale the 19yearold soldier returned to base 
with the other soviets after the game 
everything went great to be honest the thing i worried most 
about was the games final score something like 90 would have 
been terrible the border commissioner said the game ended in a 
perfect zerozero tie he said 
the game wont change much on the border however he said 
the soldiers still wont be allowed to talk or wave at each 
other overgaard said but they can smile 
