saturday in several areas apparently unaffected by the oil 
the accident occurred a week ago when the greek tanker shinoussa 
collided with two barges in the houston ship channel causing one 
barge to nearly sink oil from both barges bubbled into the 
seafoodrich bay threatening sensitive marshes birds and other 
wildlife 
the oil has washed ashore on several beaches the latest was 
houston point a marshy area north of the leading edge of the 
12mile oil slick where oil was reported friday morning 
