sudan palestine jordan and yemen voted against it he said 
libyas representative was not present and iraq did not have the 
right to vote he said 
in iraq jordans king hussein met with president sadaam 
hussein the jordanian leader announced there would be an emergency 
arab minisummit in saudi arabia on sunday to discuss the crisis 
although the united states the soviet union and other western 
countries swiftly condemned iraq and imposed sanctions on that 
nation most arab countries said little or nothing about the 
invasion until friday 
in its statement the arab league denounced the invasion and 
said it rejects and does not recognize anything resulting from 
it 
the statement handed out to reporters at the end of a twoday 
emergency meeting in cairo apparently meant that the league 
continues to recognize kuwaits emir sheik jaber alahmad alsabah 
as the countrys ruler 
we condemn the bloodshed and the destruction of buildings and 
we call on iraq to immediately and unconditionally withdraw its 
troops the statement said 
it also said the league rejects any foreign intervention or 
attempted intervention in arab affairs 
egypt was the first major arab country to condemn thursdays 
invasion 
egyptian government officials said neither president hosni 
mubarak nor other arab leaders believed iraqs claim that it 
intervened to help kuwaiti revolutionaries but they said the arab 
leaders initially held back criticism in hopes of containing the 
crisis and preserving arab unity 
first we demand that iraq withdraw its forces from kuwaiti 
territories second iraq must stop trying to change the government 
in kuwait by force and leave such internal issues to kuwaiti people 
to decide by their own free will said the egyptian foreign 
ministry statement on friday 
