potential price rise resulting from a global boycott against iraq 
should the oil from iraq and kuwait go off the market not be 
sold to anybody there is enough excess oil production capacity 
in the world to offset that loss moore said 
it seems unlikely however that the countries with the most 
unused production capacity mostly gulf arab nations including 
saudi arabia would risk antagonizing iraq by helping shield the 
united states from a price increase 
