operations by the air sea or land forces of un members 
it was believed only the fifth time in the councils 45 years 
that it has issued such a threat of sanctions 
the most recent case was the council action demanding a 
ceasefire in the iraniraq war in 1987 earlier times led to arms 
embargos against formerly whiterun rhodesia in 1967 and south 
africa in 1977 there was also a warning about sanctions in the 
first arabisraeli war in 1948 
the last un embargo came in 1967 on rhodesia it was lifted in 
1979 as the former british colony prepared for independence and 
majority rule as zimbabwe 
