the end of the cold war may produce a 
peace dividend in europe and the united states but the nations of 
southeast asia are going the other way 
defense officials reject the term arms race but all members 
of the association of southeast asian nations except the 
philippines are strengthening their military forces 
most blame uncertain conditions in the region translation the 
likely reduction of us forces compels the six asean members to 
consider providing their own defense 
it has dawned on asean that whatever happens to american bases 
in the philippines reductions in washingtons defense budget will 
mean a smaller us military presence in asia 
a buildup of strategic weapons like missiles and advanced 
fighters is occurring because military commanders are looking to 
control borders and sea lanes 
the relatively stable regional environment which we have long 
