iraqs invasion of neighboring kuwait will 
likely mean higher energy costs for much of the nation but the 
federal government says the longterm effect wont be significant 
oil experts say its difficult to predict exactly how much 
prices will rise but that higher costs on the wholesale side will 
trickle down to consumers 
concern that oil production and shipments might be disrupted in 
the middle east the source of about a quarter of us oil imports 
already has caused wholesale energy prices to soar 
in futures trading crude oil jumped more than 150 a 42gallon 
barrel while unleaded gasoline and heating oil gained more than 3 
cents a gallon 
trilby lundberg manager of a biweekly survey of gasoline prices 
that bears her name said spot checks show that some wholsale 
gasoline distributors have raised their prices around a dime a 
gallon from wednesday due to the recent increases in prices from 
their suppliers 
iraq invaded and seized control of its much smaller neighbor at 
the northern tip of the persian gulf early thursday the attack 
followed weeks of tension between the two countries over iraqi 
accusations that kuwait stole oil from its territory and was 
costing it billions of dollars in revenue by overproducing and 
helping depress the price of oil 
