possibly inflationary impact of skyrocketing crude oil prices 
linked to iraqs conquest of kuwait 
stockindex futures are contracts for future deliveries of 
baskets of stocks such as the 500 stocks tracked by the sampp 500 
index investors buy and sell the contracts to hedge against losses 
in the stock market or to speculate on stockmarket moves 
the merc and the chicago board of trade implemented the circuit 
breakers after the stockmarket crash of october 1987 which some 
critics contended was exacerbated by trading strategies that employ 
computers to trade huge blocks of stocks and index futures 
