the report was another sign that the nations faltering economy 
may be heading into a recession which could herald lower interest 
rates in the short end of the market it temporarily overshadowed 
another day of inflation worries triggered by rising oil prices 
after iraqs invasion of kuwait 
the treasurys bellwether 30year bond tumbled 1lsqb points or 
1125 per 1000 in face value on top of losses thursday of more 
than 12 the bonds yield which rises when the bonds price 
falls climbed to 856 percent from 845 percent late thursday 
economists said the unemployment report combined with a wave of 
other negative economic data in recent days normally would give the 
federal reserve enough reason to lower interest rates which would 
boost bond prices 
that sentiment was reflected among shorter maturity bills and 
bonds but the longer end of the market was gripped by the belief 
that the spike in oil prices would fuel inflation worldwide 
inflation which the fed seeks to control through monetary 
policy erodes the value of fixedincome securities such as bonds 
the data was weak enough under normal circumstances to make 
people think the fed would certainly ease said james capra 
senior vice president with shearson lehman government securities 
inc but now the issue is will the oil prices move cause the fed 
to pause or wait 
economists are concerned that a fed lower interest during a time 
of price concerns fanning inflation 
